Issues.Body:
**What version of Tailwind CSS are you using?**

4.2.2

**What build tool (or framework if it abstracts the build tool) are you using?**

Vite 8.0.8

**What version of Node.js are you using?**

v25.8.1

**What browser are you using?**

Chrome

**What operating system are you using?**

macOS

**Reproduction URL**

https://gist.github.com/janko/ee22027da0c0421daf4bb9cde3515c02

**Describe your issue**

When having imports with nested cascade layers, the built CSS is injected in different order than the `@import` statements specify. This works correctly in development with Vite dev server, but it breaks when building with Vite.

In the reproduction app, I have:

```css
/* entry.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@import "./bootstrap.css" layer(components.legacy);
@import "./app.css" layer(components);
```
```css
/* app.css */
@import "./elements.css" layer(legacy);
```
```css
/* bootstrap.css */
a {
  color: blue;
}
```
```css
/* elements.css */
a {
  color: purple;
}
```

I would expect the built output to respect the `@import` order:

```css
/* ... */
/* bootstrap.css */
@layer components.legacy {
  a {
    color: #00f;
  }
}

/* elements.css */
@layer components {
  @layer legacy {
    a {
      color: purple;
    }
  }
}
/* ... */
```

But `@bootstrap.css` rules get defined *after* `elements.css`, despite that file being imported before:

```css
/* ... */
/* elements.css */
@layer components {
  @layer legacy {
    a {
      color: purple;
    }
  }
}

/* bootstrap.css */
@layer components.legacy {
  a {
    color: #00f;
  }
}
/* ... */
```

I already tried taking `@tailwindcss/vite` out of the equation and tried to reproduce the issue only with Lightning CSS, but vanilla Lightning seems to have correct behavior.
